@node EDTW "Edit Window"

    @{FG shine}-< Edit Window >-@{FG text}


  This window is opened when you press the @{b}Edit@{ub} button in the main window. Here you can modify
 an existing site in the list below. Insert a brief description of the site and the URL.

  You can get the current URL and site description in your browser simply pressing @{b}<- Browser@{ub}
 button (see @{"settings" link CONFIG} section to choose the browser settings). You can also
 get the URL from the clipboard by clicking on the @{b}<- Clipboard@{ub} button.


  The @{b}"use delta"@{ub} option is a bit difficult to explain but very simple to understand :))
 Let's make the case you have a dynamic page (i.e. the program cannot check it from the "Last
 Modified" and "Content Length" fields). You know that the program can also check these pages
 by downloading them and then by checking their size. But if you active this option and write a
 size @{b}n@{ub} in bytes then the program will tell you that the site is changed only if the new size
 is different from the old one by @{b}n@{ub} bytes.

  For the lovers of math :)  if abs( newsize - oldsize ) >= n then the site is changed


  Below you can set the actions to perform when this URL has changes:

   @{FG shine}-@{FG text} add in changed sites list (only URL and description)

   @{FG shine}-@{FG text} send to browser in a new window (be careful to not activate this option for a great number
     of URLs, or if all that URLs have changes than you'll see a lot of browser windows on your
     screen :)))

   @{FG shine}-@{FG text} copy URL to clipboard (this action has sense only when you check single sites, otherwise
     in the clipboard you'll find only the last changed site

   @{FG shine}-@{FG text} execute command. For this one you can specify a command in the string gadget below. In this
     gadget you can also use some parameters:

       @{b}%u@{ub}  will insert the site URL

       @{b}%d@{ub}  will insert the site description

       @{b}%l@{ub}  will insert the last modify data

       @{b}%c@{ub}  will insert the content length

     @{b}IMPORTANT:@{ub} don't make too long command name strings :) (512 characters will be "accepted" but
                remember that %u and his brothers are expanded :))

  @{b}Ok@{ub} button will make the modifies, @{b}Cancel@{ub} will not. Note that when you change one of the site
  settings, than you'll have to recheck the site.

@endnode

