            - you can perform actions associated to a site from the lists context
              menus
              (10x to Efim Shuvikov)

            - now the "execute command" option works again with dynamic pages
              (10x to Efim Shuvikov)

            - added a CRC check for dynamic pages. Now if the page has no date
              and the size is the same but it contains different dates (also a
              single character) then the page will be considered changed
              (10x to Olivier Fabre)

            - in the Content Length column, when a site changes now is reported
              also the difference in bytes from the last length (none if the site
              is not changed or if the CRC is different)
              (10x to Jonas Hulten)

            - now you can log connections in files. Use this option only when you
              want to report me bugs because this options slows the program a lot
              (save log files in a RAD: to avoid damages on your hard disk if the
              program crashes)

            - cause the "great" programmers that works on Microsoft-IIS web server,
              some pages caused always an Unknown Error because this "fantastic"
              server sends randomly HTML and JavaScript code in the reply to HEAD
              requests
              (very RFCs standard compliant, damn). Now fixed.

            - seems that programmers at Netscape want to imitate Microsoft ones :)
              Netscape-FastTrack web server puts only the Content Length field and
              also incorrect because the "L" of Length is lower case (it must be upper
              case as stated in RFCs). Netscape-Enterprise (wow the big one) send Last
              Modified field but with the "M" lower case... now fixed.

            - removed a lot of situations that could cause Enforcer hits and crashes.
              However there can still be some problems.
              (10x for the report of suspected URLs)


  @{b}ver. 1.1@{ub}  - now you can check also dynamic pages by their size and you can also
              decide how many bytes of difference will make the site be considered
              changed
              (10x to Jonas Hulten for the idea)

            - removed another bug that caused an Enforcer Hit
              (10x to Gerard Cornu)

            - you can import sites from other programs (GuardAmy project, AWeb hotlist,
              IBrowse hotlist)

            - added the ADD command to the ARexx port (see the guide to know how to add
              some useful shortcuts to some browsers)

            - because of some problems ( = crash :) on some systems now you can load
              at the same time only one time the program
              (10x to Gerard Cornu)


  @{b}ver. 1.01@{ub} - removed a very buggy bug :) that caused an Enforcer Hit
              (10x to Gerard Cornu)

            - fixed a bug in the installer (the images drawer were not copied)
              (10x to Kai Weber)

            - added deutsch catalog
              (10x to Markus Fellhauer)

            - removed a bug in settings window (the columns order were changed
              every time you changed the settings)
              (10x to Surround)


  @{b}ver. 1.0@{ub}  - first public release


@endnode

@node INST "Installation"

    @{FG shine}-< Installation >-@{FG text}


  First of all double-click on the @{b}InstallEng@{ub} icon in this drawer. Follow
 the instructions and you'll install all the program in a drawer.

  After that you can start the program double-clicking on the @{b}GuardAmy@{ub} icon
 in the directory program.

  You can also install the program by hand:

   @{FG shine}-@{FG text} copy all the program directory on your hard disk

   @{FG shine}-@{FG text} copy the classes from the drawer MUI to your MUI:libs/mui/ drawer
     but @{b}only@{ub} if the ones in this archive are newer than yours

   @{FG shine}-@{FG text} start the program double-clicking on the GuardAmy icon

@endnode


