@node INFO "What is this ?"

    @{FG shine}-< Introduction >-@{FG text}


  Are you tired of checking all the sites in your bookmark every time you
 connect to the internet only to see if the same sites are changed or are
 always the same the day before ? Now with GuardAmy you can avoid this, it
 will make this work for you. Insert the URLs of the pages (or generic files
 as well), click on a button and the program will connect to all the sites
 and will report the ones that have been modified since the last time you
 checked them. You can make some actions on changed sites, for instance you can
 send the URL to a browser or to the clipboard, or you can execute a command.


  Remember also that this software is freeware, so you can copy it and use it
 without pay anything, you can spread this program only in his original format
 (i.e. this archive). Read also the @{"disclaimer" link DISC} before using the program.

@endnode

@node CONFIG "Settings Window"

    @{FG shine}-< Settings Window >-@{FG text}

  In this window you can set the program. There are 4 sections: Network, GUI, Project
 and Misc.

  @{FG shine}Network@{FG text}

    @{b}TCP-IP@{ub}: here you can set the max number of connections to make at the same time
            to check the sites. On the web you can find some pages that are dynamically
            generated from the server before beeing sent to you. For this pages is
            impossible to know the last modify date, but with GuardAmy you can check also
            them. If you select @{b}check also dynamic pages@{ub}, the program will download the
            pages without date and check if the size is different from the one it also
            knows (obviously the check process for these pages will be a bit slower). Read
            also the section of the guide for @{"add" link ADDW} and @{"edit" link EDTW} window for more infos on this
            option. You can also decide to automatically remove not found
            URLs (error @{b}404@{ub}) or gone URLs (error @{b}410@{ub}, this error is segnaled when the
            server know that the URL has moved to another place but it doen't know
            where). With the other checkmark you can tell the program to automatically
            modify the URL of moved permanently URLs (error @{b}301@{ub}, the server knows that
            the URL has been moved and knows also where, GuardAmy is able to check the new
            URL and with this option you can make the change permanent in the list).

            As you can see, you can log connections to disk. Use this option only when you
            want to report me bugs because this options slows the program a lot (save log files
            in a RAD: to avoid damages on your hard disk if the program crashes).

            @{b}Note@{ub}: moved temporarly URLs (error @{b}302@{ub}), i.e. the server knows that the
            URL has temporarly moved to another place and knows also where, are followed
            automatically by GuardAmy.

    @{b}Proxy:@{ub} you can access to sites through a proxy. Here you can set a server name and
           a port number for this proxy.

    @{b}Default Actions:@{ub} these options are the same you find in the add window, here you set
  @{b}for changed sites@{ub}  the default value to use when you add a new site to the list.
                     See the @{"add window" link ADDW} documentation for more informations.


  @{FG shine}GUI@{FG text}

    @{b}List Settings:@{ub} here you can decide what columns to show in the main window list
                   and the action to perform when you doubleclick on an item of this
                   list (@{i}send URL to browser@{ui} will use the settings in the @{b}Misc@{ub} section)

    @{b}SpeedBar Settings:@{ub} here you set the look of the main window button bar (you can see
                       the changes in realtime)

    @{b}Changed sites:@{ub} here you can set the @{"Changed Sites List Window" link CHGW}, i.e. you can select
    @{b}list settings@{ub}  an action to perform when you doubleclick on an item of this list
                   and if you want to open this window when you start GuardAmy


  @{FG shine}Project@{FG text}

    @{b}Start-Quit program:@{ub} select if you want to automatically load a project when you
                        start GuardAmy (you can choose it below) and if you want to
                        save the current project when you quit.


  @{FG shine}Misc@{FG text}

    @{b}OpenURL.library:@{ub} to send URLs to browsers GuardAmy uses the OpenURL.library
           @{b}settings@{ub}  (see the @{"FAQ" link FAQ} to know how to get this library). Here you can
                     set some options for this library.

       @{b}From browser:@{ub} first of all select the browser that you use and from which
           @{b}settings@{ub}  you want to get the URL (and site name if you set the check
                     mark below) when you press on @{b}<- Browser@{ub} buttons. See the @{"FAQ" link FAQ}
                     for more informations about this.


@endnode


@node MWIN "Main Window"

    @{FG shine}-< Main Window >-@{FG text}

  In the main window you can see a button bar, a list and a status line.

  @{FG shine}-@{FG text} pressing the buttons in the bar you can start a new project, load an existing one,
    save the current. You can also @{"add" link ADDW} a new site, @{"edit" link EDTW} an existing one from the list
    and remove current or selected items. With Check All you'll check all the sites in
    the list for search the ones that have changed, with Check Sel you'll check only
    current or selected items. @{"Chng Sites" link CHGW} will open the changed sites list window,
    @{"Settings" link CONFIG} the settings window and Help will open this guide.

  @{FG shine}-@{FG text} the list contains all the sites in the current project:

    @{b}Status@{ub} will indicate the current status or error of every item:

      @{b}Checking...@{ub} indicates that GuardAmy is checking the site on the net

      @{b}Unchecked@{ub} means this site has not been checked since program start or project load
      or if you have just added the site to the list

      @{b}Changed!!!@{ub} means the page or file has been modified since the last time you checked
      it or if you check it for the first time. If you see @{fg shine}(MT)@{fg text} or @{fg shine}(MP)@{fg text} on the left of
      Changed!!! this means the site has moved Temporarly or Permanently to another URL
      (you can automatically change the URL of MP sites, see @{"settings" link CONFIG} section).
      Instead, if you see a @{fg shine}(SZ)@{fg text} this means that the page is a dynamic one and the size
      or the CRC of the page is changed.

      @{b}Unchanged@{ub} is the opposite of Changed!!! :)

      @{b}Not found@{ub} appears when the page or file in the URL doesn't exists on the server
      (you can automatically remove these sites from the list, see @{"settings" link CONFIG} section)

      @{b}Gone@{ub} means that the server knows that the URL has been moved to another place but it
      doesn't know where. These URLs can be seen as Not found URLs, see above.

      @{b}Uncheckable@{ub} is very important: some web pages are generated dinamically from the
      http server, these pages are uncheckable because the web server doesn't send to
      you last modified data and content length. This error will appear also if the web
      server doesn't send the 2 fields at all (some very old or buggy ones). You can also
      check these pages, see the @{"settings" link CONFIG} section to know how.

      @{b}Unauthorized@{ub} and @{b}Forbidden@{ub} means that you are not allowed to access the URL.
      Sometime you'll avoid this, setting a login and password in the URL (if you know
      them :)

      @{b}Server error@{ub} means that the server to which you want to connect has temporary errors
      or disfunctions.

      @{b}Error 3xx@{ub}, @{b}Error 4xx@{ub} and @{b}Undefined error@{ub} are generic errors, please send me the
      URL of sites that makes these errors to check them.

      @{b}Cannot resolve@{ub} means that the site URL cannot be resolved from the DNS server

      @{b}Socket error@{ub} means that the program is not able to create a socket to communicate
      with the server

      @{b}Cannot connect@{ub} means that GuardAmy is not able to connect to the server

      @{b}No TCP-IP stack@{ub} will appear when you have not loaded Miami or Genesis or whatever
      create a bsdsocket.library :)))

      @{b}Send error@{ub} appears when there is an error on sending request to the server

   In the other columns you can see the site description, URL, last modify data and content
  length in bytes (between () there is the difference (+ or -) from the last length).
  You can hide some of these columns, see @{"settings" link CONFIG} section.

  Pressing the right mouse button on the list will open a context menu that contains some
  useful functions.

  @{FG shine}-@{FG text} the status line will show the current status of the program

  The menus of this window allows you to start a new project, load one from disk, save the current
  to disk, save the current to disk but with a different name, append the current project to
  an existing one, append to current project another one from disk (only in the list) and @{"import" link IMPORTW}
  the sites from other programs (GuardAmy, AWeb and IBrowse). You can also change program
  and MUI settings, read some info about MUI and GuardAmy.

@endnode


@node FAQ "F.A.Q."

    @{FG shine}-< F. A. Q. >-@{FG text}

  The most Frequently Asked Questions:
             (past and future ones :)


   @{FG shine}Q:@{FG text} Why I can get URLs only from AWeb and IBrowse and not from Voyager ?

   @{FG shine}A:@{FG text} The problem is that Voyager doesn't have an ARexx command to get site URL and site
      name :( If you really want this option, you can ask Olli to modify the ARexx port
      of V :)))


   @{FG shine}Q:@{FG text} Ok I use IBrowse 2 but I am able only to get site name, URL is always set as RESULT, so ?

   @{FG shine}A:@{FG text} I don't know if the bug is in IB2 or in my program :) I know for sure that
      all works fine with IB 1.2 but not with the version 2. (I've tested only the demo version)


   @{FG shine}Q:@{FG text} Why GuardAmy is not translated in my language ?

   @{FG shine}A:@{FG text} If you want you can do it for you by editing the file @{b}guardamy.ct@{ub} file
      in this archive and then sending it to me or making the catalog file and uploading it to
      aminet with the name guardamy_@{FG shine}XXX@{FG text}.lha (where @{FG shine}XXX@{FG text} indicates your language)... if you want
      you can translate also the .guide file ;)


   @{FG shine}Q:@{FG text} Where can I find the @{b}OpenURL.library@{ub} ?

   @{FG shine}A:@{FG text} On Aminet in the /comm/www/ directory with the name openurl@{FG shine}xx@{FG text}.lha, where @{FG shine}xx@{FG text}
      is the number of the available version (at the moment I write it's 30)



@endnode

