@node IMPORTW "Import Window"

    @{FG shine}-< Import Window >-@{FG text}

  In this window there is a list in which will be inserted the sites from the project
 or hotlist you are importing. You can select sites to import and click on the Import
 button to add these sites to the main window of GuardAmy. You can also add single
 sites by doubleclicking on them in the imported sites list. The exit button will close
 this window and will lost the sites list.


@endnode


@node TIPSTRICKS "Tips & Tricks"

    @{FG shine}-< Tips & Tricks >-@{FG text}

  Here there're some usefull things you can do to work better with GuardAmy:

   @{fg shine}-@{fg text} Thanks to the ARexx port of GuardAmy, you can configure some programs to communicate
     with GuardAmy. Copy the file @{b}GASend.rexx@{ub} that you find in the @{b}rexx@{ub} drawer of the
     program directory in the path you want (I'll call this path @{b}<scriptpath>@{ub})

       @{fg shine}o@{fg text} @{b}AWeb 3.x@{ub}  you can add some items to the context menus to send links to GuardAmy
                   from AWeb. Go to Settings menu, GUI Settings, PopUp, Link popup menu
                   then press Add and write @{b}To GuardAmy@{ub} in the Title gadget and in the
                   Command gadget add @{b}RUN <scriptpath>/GASend.rexx %u %t@{ub}
                   In this way you can send to GuardAmy the links, if you want to send
                   the link of the current page, then go to Settings menu, GUI Settings,
                   ARexx and press Add. Write @{b}To GuardAmy@{ub} in the Title gadget, choose a
                   shortcut and write @{b}<scriptpath>/GASend.rexx none none AW@{ub} in the Macro
                   gadget.

      @{fg shine}o@{fg text} @{b}IBrowse 1.x@{ub}  you can add an item to the Rexx menu. Go to Preferences, General, Rexx
                     and press the Add button. Write @{b}To GuardAmy@{ub} in the Name gadget and
                     @{b}<scriptpath>/GASend.rexx none none IB@{ub} in the Macro gadget.

      @{fg shine}o@{fg text} @{b}Others@{ub}  make some experiments with other programs and the GASend.rexx script and
                tell me of the results :)

      @{b}Note:@{ub} the GASend.rexx script will automatically start GuardAmy if it's not
            loaded. To make this you have to modify the file @{b}rexx/GuardAmy.s@{ub} where
            you'll specify the exact GuardAmy path and the file @{b}rexx/GASend.rexx@{ub}
            at line 8 where you'll specify the exact path of the file GuardAmy.s

@endnode

@node AREXX "ARexx Port"

    @{FG shine}-< ARexx Port >-@{FG text}


  The ARexx port of GuardAmy is named GUARDAMY and has the following commands:


  Command:   @{b}quit@{ub}
  Template:  FORCE/S
  Action:    quit the program

  Command:   @{b}hide@{ub}
  Template:
  Action:    hide (iconify) the program window

  Command:   @{b}deactivate@{ub}
  Template:
  Action:    deactivate the program window

  Command:   @{b}show@{ub}
  Template:
  Action:    unhide (uniconify) the program window

  Command:   @{b}activate@{ub}
  Template:
  Action:    activate the program window

  Command:   @{b}info@{ub}
  Template:  ITEM/A
  Action:    give some info on this program

  Command:   @{b}help@{ub}
  Template:  FILE/A
  Action:    save a file with the arexx commands

